text.section:
"Lead-safe housing" means a rental dwelling unit that:
Is certified to be lead-free in accordance with § 6-804 of this subtitle;
Was constructed after 1978;
Is deemed to be lead-safe by the Department in accordance with criteria established by the Department by regulation; or
Is certified to be in compliance with § 6-815(a) of this subtitle and:
In which all windows are either lead-free or have been treated so that all friction surfaces are lead-free;
In which lead-contaminated dust levels are determined to be within abatement clearance levels established by the Department by regulation, within a time frame established by the Department by regulation; and
Which is subject to ongoing maintenance and testing as specified by the Department by regulation.

section.section:
"Rental dwelling unit" does not include:
An area not used for living, sleeping, eating, cooking, or sanitation, such as an unfinished basement;
A unit within a hotel, motel, or similar seasonal or transient facility;
An area which is secured and inaccessible to occupants; or
A unit which is not offered for rent.
